text
@Different files are listed with short descriptions of what they are or what they do.  The status of any package that has been checked for correctness is listed, including any useful notes.  Anything that doesn't have a status or description needs to have one added.  Anything that is broken, incorrect, or dated will have a bad status. 

Items that are presently being tested are noted by the name of the tester after the tool/file/package's name.  (e.g. `gen.sh sean')

---

root files
-----------------
gen.sh
  status: ok
  desc: main package builder/install script
Cakefile
  status: ok
  desc: calls gen.sh
Cakefile.defs
  status: ok
  desc: definition of different architecture-specific build settings
Cakefile.lib
  status: ok
  desc: cakefile used for building a library
Cakefile.prog
  status: ok
  desc: cakefile used for building programs/tools
Cakefile.rules
  status: ok
  desc: patterns used during install
Makefile
  status: ok
  desc: calls gen.sh
Makefile.defs
  status: ok
Makefile.rules
  status: ok
makefile.vc
makemsc.hdr
mtype.sh
newbindir.sh
setup.sh

README
  status: bad
  extremely dated readme about the entire package last updated 1995; would recommend using gnu convention of having a README|INSTALL|LICENSE|... set of files

Tools\Binaries
--------------
Listed below are the binaries that get installed after compilation.  The testing status is listed where relevant.

